  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1988-05-05", 
    "text": "Amends the Miller Act to require payment bonds for contracts and subcontracts with the United States which exceed $25,000 in amount. (Current provisions require payment bonds for such contracts for the construction, alteration, or repair of any public building or public work.) Sets forth the rights of subcontractors under payment bonds. Repeals the right of the armed forces and the Department of Transportation to waive payment bond requirements."
  }, 
